Add a question randomization system to the quiz logic.

Context:
- There are 10 beginner questions and 10 mid-level questions stored in a quiz data file
- Beginner sessions should present 5 random questions
- Mid-level sessions should present 7 random questions
- The same question should not appear twice in a single session
- Each new session should feel different and unpredictable

Implementation requirements:
- Filter questions by level first
- Randomize the order only once when the quiz session starts
- Select the required number of questions per level
- Store the randomized question set in state
- Do not reshuffle on re-render
- Keep the logic simple and readable

Create a small helper function to shuffle questions.
Avoid external libraries.
Show the full updated code for the main page file and explain what changed.
